main event: An object, silver in color with a very pronounced vapor trail, was observed moving at a very high rate of speed in the sky near Mannasquam, New Jersey on October 23, 1957.
interesting points: The object was observed to be at a very high altitude, moving at a speed estimated to be between 222-235 mph and an altitude of 32-33,333 feet.
The object made several turns, starting northeast and ending southwest.
The observer compared the speed and altitude of the object to an aircraft in the vicinity, but noted that the estimates were unusual for the time of the sighting.
The report was made after an extended delay to G2 1st Army, who then relayed the report.
The weather conditions were clear at the time of the sighting.
sighted object: a silver, high-altitude object with a pronounced vapor trail
